      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "### hERG-relevant \u201cpharmacophore\u201d check\nTypical high-risk hERG blockers often have:\n- **A basic, readily protonated amine** (often tertiary)  \n- **Two hydrophobic/aromatic regions** flanking it (or one aromatic + one hydrophobe)  \n- **A shape/length that spans the cavity** and can \u03c0-stack with aromatic residues (e.g., Tyr/Phe)",
