      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "### Features increasing hERG risk\n1. **Presence of a protonatable nitrogen (secondary amine)**  \n   - hERG binding is often strengthened by a **cation\u2013\u03c0 / electrostatic interaction** between a protonated amine and the channel cavity.\n2. **Substantial lipophilic bulk + aromatic ring**  \n   - The phenyl ring plus multiple hydrophobic substituents can support **hydrophobic/\u03c0 interactions** in the pore.\n3. **Overall 3D bulk/length**  \n   - Multiple rings and substituents suggest the molecule can occupy a significant volume, potentially fitting the hERG cavity.",
