      "step_index": 8,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "### Features decreasing hERG risk\n1. **Only one aromatic ring (limited \u03c0 surface)**  \n   - Many potent hERG blockers have **two** aromatic systems or extended \u03c0 character; here, the second \u201cdomain\u201d is mostly **non-aromatic**.\n2. **Amine basicity likely moderate (not strongly cationic)**  \n   - The N is in an unsaturated heterocycle and near polar functionality; that often **reduces pKa**, lowering the fraction protonated at physiological pH \u2192 weaker hERG binding.\n3. **Higher polarity / H-bonding (ethers + carbonyl + alcohol)**  \n   - Added polarity can reduce nonspecific membrane partitioning and reduce affinity for the hydrophobic cavity (though this is not a guarantee).",
